<subSubSection pageId="20" pageNumber="21" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="20.[151,1436,338,724]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
COMMENTS. Numerous samples of Belizean material of 
<taxonomicName authority="(BMNH)" baseAuthorityName="BMNH" box="[908,1149,498,524]" class="Insecta" family="Aleyrodidae" genus="Aleurodicus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="araujoi">
<emphasis box="[908,1030,498,523]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">A. araujoi</emphasis>
(BMNH)
</taxonomicName>
have been identified in comparison with syntypic material from 
<collectingCountry box="[628,720,538,564]" name="Mexico" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Mexico</collectingCountry>
, loaned by UCD in connection with a study of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Zootaxa" baseAuthorityYear="1835" box="[1270,1436,538,564]" class="Insecta" family="Aleyrodidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Aleurodicinae">Aleurodicinae</taxonomicName>
in 
<collectingCountry box="[180,255,578,604]" name="Belize" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Belize</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Martin, J. H." box="[270,429,578,604]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" pagination="1 - 119" refId="ref44057" refString="Martin, J. H. (2004) The whiteflies of Belize (Hemiptera: Aleyrodidae) Part 1 - introduction and account of the subfamily Aleurodicinae Quaintance &amp; Baker. Zootaxa, 681, 1 - 119." type="journal article" year="2004">Martin, 2004</bibRefCitation>
), in which publication host plant records in 
<collectingCountry box="[939,1014,578,604]" name="Belize" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Belize</collectingCountry>
were tabulated. This species clearly belongs to the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bondar" authorityYear="1923" box="[323,445,618,643]" class="Insecta" family="Aleyrodidae" genus="Aleurodicus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="capiangae">
<emphasis box="[323,445,618,643]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">capiangae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
/ 
<taxonomicName box="[467,552,618,643]" class="Insecta" family="Aleyrodidae" genus="Aleurodicus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dugesii">
<emphasis box="[467,552,618,643]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">dugesii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group, and may be recognised by use of the key to species, p. 15.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="20.[151,1436,338,724]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
A sample of puparia from mistletoe in 
<collectingCountry box="[661,790,658,684]" name="Costa Rica" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Costa Rica</collectingCountry>
(BMNH) has its puparia rather darkly pigmented, and other slight differences from the extensive Belizean material, but is considered likely to be conspecific.
</paragraph>
